UID:pulpdeb@cfgmgmtcamp.eu
SUMMARY:Managing large Debian repositories with Pulp (and less than 50GiB of RAM)
ORGANIZER:Quirin Pamp
CATEGORIES:talk
DTSTAMP:20181231T000000Z
TZID:Europe-Brussels
DTSTART:20190204T150000
DTEND:20190204T155500
DESCRIPTION;ALTREP="https://cfgmgmtcamp.eu/schedule/monday/pulpdeb/":Managing large Debian repositories with Pulp (and less than 50GiB of RAM)
X-ALT-DESC;FMTTYPE=text/html:@"<!DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC ""-//W3C//DTD HTML 3.2//EN""><HTML><BODY><p>Pulp is a platform for software repository management.<br />
The pulp_deb plugin adds Apt-repository support for Debian packages.<br />
Until recently, the pulp_deb implementation did not scale well for large repositories.<br />
Synchronizing a full Debian or Ubuntu release (typically containing around 50,000 Packages)
would routinely take hours before falling victim to the OOM-killer.<br />
This talk discusses the changes we employed to fix this lamentable state of affairs.<br />
It concludes with lessons learned for the development of pulp_deb 3.</p>
</BODY></HTML>";
URL:https://cfgmgmtcamp.eu/schedule/monday/pulpdeb/
LOCATION:3.pulp
CLASS:PUBLIC
STATUS:CONFIRMED
END:VEVENT
