UID:pulp3@cfgmgmtcamp.eu
SUMMARY:Pulp 3: Ready for a Test Drive
ORGANIZER:Austin Macdonald
CATEGORIES:talk
DTSTAMP:20181231T000000Z
TZID:Europe-Brussels
DTSTART:20190204T140000
DTEND:20190204T145500
DESCRIPTION;ALTREP="https://cfgmgmtcamp.eu/schedule/monday/pulp3/":Pulp 3: Ready for a Test Drive
X-ALT-DESC;FMTTYPE=text/html:@"<!DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC ""-//W3C//DTD HTML 3.2//EN""><HTML><BODY><p>Pulp is a platform for managing repositories of software packages, and its plugin architecture allows management of any type of content.<br />
Pulp&rsquo;s web API enables users to synchronize, upload, and publish versioned repositories with simple but flexible workflows.<br />
This presentation will highlight simplified installation and deployment, better performance, new features,
and a growing collection of plugins including rpm, python, docker, ansible, chef, ruby, file, and more in development.<br />
Pulp 3 is approaching maturity and is ready for you to test drive.</p>
</BODY></HTML>";
