UID:fromback@cfgmgmtcamp.eu
SUMMARY:Tool migration - from Puppet to mgmt and back
ORGANIZER:Felix Frank
CATEGORIES:talk
DTSTAMP:20181229T000000Z
TZID:Europe-Brussels
DTSTART:20190204T150000
DTEND:20190204T155500
DESCRIPTION;ALTREP="https://cfgmgmtcamp.eu/schedule/monday/fromback/":Tool migration - from Puppet to mgmt and back
X-ALT-DESC;FMTTYPE=text/html:@"<!DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC ""-//W3C//DTD HTML 3.2//EN""><HTML><BODY><p>Switching out the back bone of your automation tool chain is usually painful.<br />
It likely involves rewriting all your infrastructure code,
and will either require a scary over-night cut-off, or a period in which two tools run concurrently,
with operators carefully shifting functionality one step at a time.</p>

<p>With mgmt&rsquo;s support for Puppet code, migrating becomes a lot more natural.<br />
This session does a deep dive and shows how mgmt will allow you to use and maintain a mixed code base of both Puppet&rsquo;s and mgmt&rsquo;s DSLs.</p>
</BODY></HTML>";
URL:https://cfgmgmtcamp.eu/schedule/monday/fromback/
LOCATION:3.mgmt
CLASS:PUBLIC
STATUS:CONFIRMED
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
METHOD:PUBLISH
UID:uxuicfgtool@cfgmgmtcamp.eu
SUMMARY:UX challenges of a UI-centric config management tool
ORGANIZER:Raphael Gauthier
CATEGORIES:talk
DTSTAMP:20181229T000000Z
TZID:Europe-Brussels
DTSTART:20190204T163000
DTEND:20190204T172500
DESCRIPTION;ALTREP="https://cfgmgmtcamp.eu/schedule/monday/uxuicfgtool/":UX challenges of a UI-centric config management tool
X-ALT-DESC;FMTTYPE=text/html:@"<!DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC ""-//W3C//DTD HTML 3.2//EN""><HTML><BODY><p>One of Rudder&rsquo;s main focuses is its comprehensive graphical user interface,
which allows users to view and manage its configurations without writing a line of code.<br />
The user experience and interface considerations for a tool as technical and complex,
and with such potential to break things as a configuration management tool are certainly a challenge,
and in some ways in unchartered territory. Rudder&rsquo;s frontend developer will present an analysis of the situation,
the issues encountered and the approach adopted for the improvement of UX and UI planned for 2019.</p>
</BODY></HTML>";
URL:https://cfgmgmtcamp.eu/schedule/monday/uxuicfgtool/
LOCATION:3.rudder
CLASS:PUBLIC
STATUS:CONFIRMED
END:VEVENT
