METHOD:PUBLISH
UID:mgmtroad@cfgmgmtcamp.eu
SUMMARY:Mgmt Config: The Road to 0.1
ORGANIZER:James 'purpleidea' Shubin
CATEGORIES:talk
DTSTAMP:20181228T000000Z
TZID:Europe-Brussels
DTSTART:20190204T140000
DTEND:20190204T145500
DESCRIPTION;ALTREP="https://cfgmgmtcamp.eu/schedule/monday/mgmtroad/":Mgmt Config: The Road to 0.1
X-ALT-DESC;FMTTYPE=text/html:@"<!DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC ""-//W3C//DTD HTML 3.2//EN""><HTML><BODY><p>Real-time, autonomous, automation.</p>

<p>Mgmt is a real-time automation tool that is fast and safe.<br />
As we get closer to a 0.1 release that we&rsquo;ll recommend as &ldquo;production ready&rdquo;,
we&rsquo;ll look at the last remaining features that we&rsquo;re aiming to land by then.<br />
We&rsquo;ll explain and demo the import and module system, classes, and native functions.</p>

<p>It uses a real-time, reactive programming language to model the desired state over time,
and a powerful event-driven engine to apply this state.<br />
We&rsquo;ll also show some exciting real-time demos that include scheduling, finite state machines, and remote execution.<br />
Finally we&rsquo;ll talk about some of the future designs we&rsquo;re planning and
make it easy for new users to get involved and help shape the project.</p>
</BODY></HTML>";
URL:https://cfgmgmtcamp.eu/schedule/monday/mgmtroad/
LOCATION:3.mgmt
CLASS:PUBLIC
STATUS:CONFIRMED
END:VEVENT
