METHOD:PUBLISH
UID:incidentcode@cfgmgmtcamp.eu
SUMMARY:Incident Resolution as Code
ORGANIZER:Julien Pivotto
CATEGORIES:talk
DTSTAMP:20181226T000000Z
TZID:Europe-Brussels
DTSTART:20190204T163000
DTEND:20190204T172500
DESCRIPTION;ALTREP="https://cfgmgmtcamp.eu/schedule/monday/incidentcode/":Incident Resolution as Code
X-ALT-DESC;FMTTYPE=text/html:@"<!DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC ""-//W3C//DTD HTML 3.2//EN""><HTML><BODY><p>In this talk I will go in details about how we quickly resolve incidents using Prometheus and ansible.</p>

<p>Come and discover how we linked the monitoring, queuing systems and orchestration to do unattended incident management.</p>

<p>One of the main advantages of this is that we can apply technical remediation or mitigation from business metrics,
even if things happen at different levels.</p>

<p>All of this working anywhere Prometheus and ansible run, so not only in a kube env, but also in a traditional infrastructure.</p>
</BODY></HTML>";
URL:https://cfgmgmtcamp.eu/schedule/monday/incidentcode/
LOCATION:3.ansible
CLASS:PUBLIC
STATUS:CONFIRMED
